15:05.069 --> 15:07.321
No!

15:09.156 --> 15:10.616
[ Both Scream ]

15:10.699 --> 15:12.118
[Cable Car Bell Clanging]

15:12.201 --> 15:13.744
[ Relieved Sighs]

15:13.828 --> 15:15.121
End of the line!

15:15.204 --> 15:16.580
[ Both Scream ]

15:16.664 --> 15:18.999
[ Both Moaning ]

15:19.083 --> 15:21.085
Hey. You're not John Ritter.

15:21.168 --> 15:23.212
And you ain't that gorilla
from the zoo.

15:23.295 --> 15:24.797
Meh.
Eh.

15:28.467 --> 15:31.637
Okay, you filthy booze bags,
it's 2:00 a.m.

15:31.720 --> 15:33.806
So, uh, who's
the designated driver?

15:33.889 --> 15:35.641
It was Andy.

15:37.893 --> 15:39.854
[ Laughing]

15:39.937 --> 15:43.107
No one's ever won Moe's
“drink a gallon of gin” challenge.

15:43.190 --> 15:44.984
And no one ever will.

15:45.067 --> 15:46.485
Ah, life is good.

15:46.569 --> 15:48.779
HeY, what happened?

15:48.863 --> 15:50.614
It's bright in the middle
of the night!

15:50.698 --> 15:53.909
You know what this reminds
me of- my Icelandic boyhood.

15:53.993 --> 15:56.036
It's this new
anticrime dealie.

15:56.120 --> 15:58.414
The mayor turned
the street lights way up.

15:58.497 --> 16:01.083
My daughter Lisa feels
really strongly about it.

16:01.167 --> 16:02.877
Pro or con?
I don't know.

16:02.960 --> 16:04.670
What am I-
superdad?

16:04.753 --> 16:07.256
Boy, this light has really
screwed up the animals.

16:07.339 --> 16:08.507
[Chirps]

16:10.384 --> 16:11.886
[ Squawking ]

16:13.554 --> 16:17.224
<i>I'll</i> bet somewhere
there's a horse drinking coffee.

16:21.979 --> 16:24.148
I haven't slept
in seven days.

16:24.231 --> 16:27.151
And I've gotten
so much ironing done.

16:27.234 --> 16:31.447
“Live from New York,
it's Saturday night!”

16:31.530 --> 16:33.240
♪♪ [Humming]

16:33.324 --> 16:37.495
Dad, this lack of sleep is
making Morn and Maggie crazy.

16:37.578 --> 16:41.373
Don't you think you're overreacting,
talking gum-ball machine?

16:41.457 --> 16:43.334
...or an assemblyman
on the take.

16:43.417 --> 16:44.710
Forget it, Bart.
It's so bright out...

16:44.793 --> 16:49.048
you can't see anything in the
sky except the Fox satellite.

16:49.131 --> 16:51.091
[Squeaking, Clanking]

16:51.175 --> 16:53.010
No, Lise. I got my eyes
on the prize-

16:53.093 --> 16:55.012
the hood ornament
I desperately want...

16:55.095 --> 16:57.014
for reasons
I can no longer remember.

16:57.097 --> 16:59.558
The only thing stopping me
is those lights!

16:59.642 --> 17:01.977
[ Gasps ]
Bart, I just realized...

17:02.061 --> 17:04.771
we both want the same thing-
darkness!

17:04.855 --> 17:07.023
And we can get it
if we work together.

17:07.107 --> 17:09.401
With my brain and your-

17:09.484 --> 17:11.612
your... assistance-

17:11.694 --> 17:13.364
You can say it.
I add nothing.

17:13.446 --> 17:16.075
- <i>[ Bird</i> Ca <i>Wing ]</i> - You can't
have lights without power,

17:16.157 --> 17:18.536
and all the power
comes from here.

17:18.618 --> 17:20.538
How'd you get Dad
to go along with this?

17:20.621 --> 17:23.374
In his sleep-deprived state,
he's very suggestible.

17:23.457 --> 17:27.377
Okay, Dad. You are now playing
patty-cake with Maggie.

17:27.461 --> 17:29.338
[Mumbling Gibberish]

17:29.421 --> 17:32.716
<i>[ Male Electronic: Voice ] Pe/m recognized.
A ccess grantee'.</i>

17:32.800 --> 17:35.302
Aw, my baby's first words.

17:38.556 --> 17:39.765
[Murmurs]

17:39.848 --> 17:43.894
Now we merely push this switch
to “Overload.”

17:43.978 --> 17:46.397
Yet once we do,
we'll be breaking the law.

17:46.480 --> 17:49.567
Can good truly come
from civil disobedience?

17:49.650 --> 17:51.402
Gandhi thought so, but-

17:51.485 --> 17:53.571
Gandhi also said,
“Less talk, more rock!”

17:53.654 --> 17:56.699
[ Generators Whirring ]

17:56.782 --> 17:58.993
[ Electricity Crackling ]

17:59.076 --> 18:01.954
[ People Exclaiming ]
[ Lightbulbs Popping ]

18:04.999 --> 18:05.958
[Guns Cocking]

18:06.041 --> 18:07.835
Uh-oh. All the lights are out.

18:07.918 --> 18:10.296
You better get the entire
force working on this.

18:10.379 --> 18:12.131
But, Chief,
we are the entire force.

18:12.214 --> 18:13.966
Okay. We gotta start
recruiting, Lou.

18:20.139 --> 18:23.183
Ach! Look at all
those shards of glass!

18:23.267 --> 18:25.436
<i>I'll</i> catch 'em on my tongue
for luck.

18:25.519 --> 18:27.021
Ow! Ow!

18:27.104 --> 18:28.814
[ Groaning ]
Ow! Ow!

18:28.897 --> 18:31.775
It worked.
I got my sky back.

18:31.859 --> 18:33.027
Dad, look!

18:33.110 --> 18:36.238
Night! Glorious night!

18:36.322 --> 18:38.407
[ Bleating ]

18:38.490 --> 18:40.993
[ Mooing ]

18:41.076 --> 18:44.204
[Growling, Whimpering]

18:44.872 --> 18:47.124
[Snoring]

18:47.207 --> 18:48.375
Uh-oh.

18:48.459 --> 18:51.086
[ Crowd Clamoring ] There they are!
Let's get 'em!

18:51.170 --> 18:53.589
I can't read porno
by candlelight!

18:53.672 --> 18:55.382
Who am I- Abe Lincoln!

18:55.466 --> 18:58.385
I say tear them
limb from limb!

18:58.469 --> 19:00.095
[ Clamoring ]

19:00.179 --> 19:02.389
[ Gasps ]
Look.

19:02.473 --> 19:05.351
[ Crowd Exclaiming, Gasping ] Huh?
Oh, wow!

19:05.434 --> 19:08.187
[All Murmuring]
It's so beautiful.

19:08.270 --> 19:09.813
I'm not angry anymore.

19:09.897 --> 19:12.483
Whoa, I don't need drugs
to enjoy this.

19:12.566 --> 19:14.068
Just to enhance it.

19:14.151 --> 19:16.904
<i>♪♪ [ Acoustic Guitar] [ Man]
♪ Starry, starry night ♪</i>

19:18.530 --> 19:21.909
<i>♪ Paint your palette
blue and gray;</i>

19:23.452 --> 19:26.705
<i>♪ Look out
on a summefls day,»</i>

19:26.789 --> 19:30.292
<i>♪ With eyes that know
the darkness in my soul ♪</i>

19:30.376 --> 19:32.503
I wish Jimmy the Snitch
could see this.

19:32.586 --> 19:35.130
[ Man, Muffled ]
Well, just open the trunk!

19:35.214 --> 19:38.425
And I thought this was
gonna be a <i>bad</i> night.

19:41.637 --> 19:43.555
Oh! Great Glayvin
in a Glad bag!

19:43.639 --> 19:46.809
That meteor contains
carbon-based molecules.

19:46.892 --> 19:50.145
I may be able to prove the
existence of life in outer space.

19:50.229 --> 19:52.523
Ha, ha!
Shut up.

19:55.192 --> 19:57.611
[ Marge ]
Whoa.

19:57.695 --> 20:00.447
This is even better
than our screen saver.

20:00.531 --> 20:02.449
And I love
our screen saver.

20:02.533 --> 20:05.411
Nicely done, Lisa.
Thanks, Mom.

20:05.494 --> 20:08.122
I wish God were alive
to see this.

20:08.205 --> 20:09.915
<i>♪ They would not listen ♪</i>

20:09.998 --> 20:12.626
<i>♪ They're not listening still ♪</i>

20:14.420 --> 20:19.633
<i>♪ Perhaps the y never willy,»</i>

20:22.970 --> 20:25.097
<i>[ Desmond Narrating]
Ameflcan Boneheads...</i>

20:25.180 --> 20:28.475
A Day in the Life
of Springfield Elementary.

20:28.559 --> 20:31.311
<i>Where do you think
you will be in seven years?</i>

20:31.395 --> 20:33.480
<i>I'm gonna live with
Underground Grandma.</i>

20:33.564 --> 20:36.024
<i>I'm gonna go to a two-year
technical school,</i>

20:36.108 --> 20:37.776
<i>then work in a garage.</i>

20:37.860 --> 20:40.195
<i>[ Groaning] Sell-out! Yuppie!</i>

20:40.279 --> 20:41.572
<i>Soccer mom!</i>

20:41.655 --> 20:44.533
<i>I 'II be batting .352
in the majors!</i>

20:45.868 --> 20:47.870
<i>[ Grunting]</i>

20:54.752 --> 20:56.420
<i>Yes!</i>

20:57.171 --> 20:59.006
<i>Did you get that, Simon?</i>

20:59.089 --> 21:00.591
<i>Brilliant!
[ Inhales ]</i>

